  "text": "AEs were considered minor when they required simple or ambulatory care (late dislodged tube, peristomal leak, wound infection, granuloma formation, minor wound bleeding or small hematoma). Major AEs included peritonitis, buried bumper syndrome (BBS), septicemia, aspiration pneumonia, hemorrhage, gastric perforation, gastrocolocutaneous fistula and any AEs requiring a repeat procedure, surgical or endoscopic treatment, or blood transfusion [CITATION_1] .",
